
  Summary: Formalized Search Filter Criteria Types

  Files Created

  1. /core/models/search/__init__.py - Module exports
  - Exports all filter dataclasses and enums

  2. /core/models/search/filter_enums.py - Filter operation enums
  - FilterOperator - Query operators (EQ, NE, GT, GTE, LT, LTE, IN, CONTAINS, BETWEEN)
  - SearchSortOrder - Sort ordering (RELEVANCE, CREATED_*, PRIORITY_*, DUE_DATE_*, PROGRESS_*, STREAK_*)

  3. /core/models/search/filters.py - Filter dataclasses

  | Filter Class           | Domain     | Key Fields                                                                                  |
  |------------------------|------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
  | BaseSearchFilters      | All        | query, status, domain, related_uid, relationship_type, user_uid, limit                      |
  | DateRangeFilters       | All        | days_ahead, days_back, start_date, end_date                                                 |
  | TaskSearchFilters      | Tasks      | priority, fulfills_goal_uid, reinforces_habit_uid, applies_knowledge_uid, include_completed |
  | GoalSearchFilters      | Goals      | timeframe, category, parent_goal_uid, min/max_progress, target_date                         |
  | HabitSearchFilters     | Habits     | frequency, min/max_current_streak, supports_goal_uid, completed_today                       |
  | EventSearchFilters     | Events     | event_type, event_date, recurring_only, supports_goal_uid, exclude_cancelled                |
  | ChoiceSearchFilters    | Choices    | urgency, affects_goal_uid, min/max_impact_score, deadline, pending_only                     |
  | PrincipleSearchFilters | Principles | strength, principle_category, active_only, needs_review, guiding_goal_uid                   |

  Protocol Update

  /core/services/protocols/search_protocols.py - Added search_filtered() method
  async def search_filtered(self, filters: "BaseSearchFilters") -> Result[list[T]]:
      """Type-safe filtered search using domain-specific filter dataclass."""

  Usage Example

  from core.models.search import TaskSearchFilters
  from core.models.shared_enums import ActivityStatus, Priority

  # Create type-safe filters (IDE autocomplete + MyPy verification)
  filters = TaskSearchFilters(
      status=ActivityStatus.IN_PROGRESS,
      priority=Priority.HIGH,
      fulfills_goal_uid="goal:health-2025",
      include_completed=False,
      limit=20
  )

  # Convert to backend query params
  params = filters.to_query_params()
  # {'status': 'in_progress', 'priority': 'high', 'fulfills_goal_uid': 'goal:health-2025', 'status__ne': 'completed', 'limit': 20}

  Type Safety Benefits

  1. Enum fields - status, priority, domain, frequency use proper enums
  2. Frozen dataclasses - Immutable filter objects
  3. IDE autocomplete - All fields discoverable
  4. MyPy verification - Type errors caught at compile time
  5. Self-documenting - Filter capabilities are explicit in the type definition

